    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Primula \u00d7 brueggeri are primarily made from its flowers and leaves, which are rich in phenolic compounds and flavonoids. Primula tea is a decoction made by steeping the dried flowers and leaves in hot water to relieve digestive issues and coughs, with a recommended dosage of 1-2 teaspoons per cup. A tincture is made by soaking the plant material in a solvent, typically ethanol, to create a concentrated liquid extract used to treat respiratory issues and infections, with a recommended dosage of 20-30 drops per day. An infusion is a liquid extract made by steeping the plant material in cold water, used to treat sore throats and skin irritations, with a recommended dosage of 1-2 cups per day. Additionally, a salve and infused oil can be made from the plant's leaves and flowers, used topically to treat minor cuts and skin irritations.",
